I")<p>I am most interested in breaking things down to their most atomic form.  From that perspective, FBP and discrete-event-based components have the same roots.</p>

<p>The deepest roots are:</p>

<p>1) concurrency<br />
2) isolation.</p>

<p>If you have both, then you can plug components together like LEGO blocks and it “doesn’t matter” how you implement components (pure functions, stateful, etc. - it’s all hidden from view via isolation).</p>

